---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
	"@context": "https://schema.org",
	"@type": "FAQPage",
	"mainEntity": [
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "How is net worth different from cashflow?",
			"acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Net worth is a snapshot of your assets minus liabilities, showing what you have accumulated. Cashflow is the monthly movement of money in and out, determining your financial sustainability. While net worth tells you where you are, positive cashflow is the engine that drives future wealth. You can have a high net worth but face ruin with negative cashflow; conversely, strong cashflow builds lasting financial freedom." }
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "Why no monthly expenses in the Net Worth Calculator?",
			"acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Net worth operates fundamentally as a balance sheet concept, providing a precise snapshot of your financial position at a specific moment in time by strictly measuring the difference between what you own, known as assets, and what you owe, referred to as liabilities. This calculation answers the critical question of your current equity without factoring in the timing of transactions or daily spending habits. In contrast, monthly expenses belong entirely to the realm of cashflow analysis, which tracks the dynamic movement of money entering and leaving your accounts over a period to determine income versus expenditures. Attempting to mix these two distinct financial frameworks within a single calculation creates significant distortion, as blending balance sheet data with cashflow metrics obscures the true nature of both your accumulated wealth and your daily financial health, potentially leading to inaccurate assessments of your stability and future potential. To gain clarity and avoid these analytical errors, it is essential to keep these metrics completely separate, utilizing Engine B for a detailed examination of your monthly spending, income gaps, and overall cashflow health, as this dedicated tool is specifically designed to handle the complexities of cashflow analysis without the noise of balance sheet variables interfering with your financial planning." }
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "Can I add my own categories?",
			"acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, you have full flexibility to customize your categories. Every panel features an Add button that allows you to instantly create a new custom row; simply click it, enter your desired category name, and the row will appear immediately for your use. These custom rows are fully manageable, meaning you can delete them at any time by clicking the X button next to them. Please note, however, that default rows cannot be removed to ensure your core data structure remains intact. This design gives you the best of both worlds: a stable foundation with essential default categories while allowing you to tailor the tool precisely to your unique financial needs by adding and removing your own custom entries as required." }
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "How accurate are the compound interest projections?",
			"acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Compound interest projections are directional planning tools rather than guaranteed predictions, as they assume consistent returns that real-world markets rarely provide. While the calculations mathematically follow the inputs you provide, actual investment performance fluctuates due to economic conditions, inflation, and market volatility. For context, historical averages for the S&P 500 hover around 10% annually, or approximately 7% when adjusted for inflation, but past performance does not ensure future results. These projections should be used to visualize potential growth trajectories and set realistic financial goals, not as absolute guarantees of future wealth. It is essential to treat these figures as a baseline for strategic planning, understanding that your actual returns may vary significantly depending on the specific assets chosen and the timing of market entry and exit." }
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "What is the difference between compound and simple interest?",
			"acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The fundamental difference between simple and compound interest lies in how each calculates returns. Simple interest is calculated solely on the original principal amount, meaning the interest earned remains constant throughout the term and never compounds. This method is typically used for short-term loans, fixed deposits, and specific types of bonds where predictable, linear growth is desired. In contrast, compound interest generates returns on both the initial principal and the previously accumulated interest, creating a snowball effect that leads to exponential growth over time. Because of this powerful compounding mechanism, it is the standard for most long-term investments, savings accounts, and mortgages, where the goal is to maximize wealth accumulation or, in the case of loans, where the debt can grow rapidly if not managed. Understanding this distinction is crucial: simple interest offers stability and simplicity, while compound interest offers the potential for significantly higher returns or costs, depending on whether you are investing or borrowing." }
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "How do I use the Simple Interest calculator for a loan?",
			"acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "To calculate loan details, navigate to Engine C and select the Simple Interest tab, then activate Loan mode. Enter the required fields: the loan principal, the annual interest rate from your lender, and the loan term. Once input, the calculator instantly displays your total interest payable, the total amount to repay, and the precise monthly installment, giving you a clear picture of your repayment obligations before you commit." }
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "Which currencies are supported?",
			"acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The platform offers comprehensive currency flexibility with a main dropdown supporting all 180 national fiat currencies, which are easily searchable by name or ISO code. For alternative assets, Gold (XAU) and Silver (XAG) are directly selectable on the Bullion Metals row within the Assets panel in Engine A. Similarly, major cryptocurrencies including Bitcoin (BTC), Ethereum (ETH), and Solana (SOL) can be chosen on the Digital Assets row in the same panel. Regardless of the asset class you select, all calculations update instantly to reflect your current financial snapshot accurately." }
		}
	]
};
---

<Layout>
	<section class="hero-section">
		<div class="hero-bg">
			<div class="grid-pattern"></div>
			<div class="gradient-orb orb-1"></div>
			<div class="gradient-orb orb-2"></div>
		</div>
		<div class="hero-content">
			<div class="hero-badge">
				<span class="badge-dot pulse"></span>
				<span class="badge-text">V3.0 Three Engine Release</span>
			</div>
			<h1 class="hero-title">
				<span class="title-line">NetWorthCurve</span>
                <span class="title-line">Start Your Curve Today</span>
				<span class="title-line accent">Sovereign Wealth Management System</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="hero-subtitle">NetWorthCurve is the premier privacy-first financial planning platform designed for individuals who refuse to compromise their data security for convenience. Unlike traditional cloud-based tools, we specialize in local-first financial sovereignty, providing institutional-grade net worth, cash flow, and interest analysis entirely within your browser. Our niche is serving privacy-conscious investors, crypto holders, and self-reliant individuals who need to analyze their wealth without creating an account or any logins.</p>
			
			<div class="hero-metrics" style="margin-bottom: 60px;">
				<div class="metric"><span class="metric-value">100%</span><span class="metric-label">Client-Side</span></div>
				<div class="metric-divider"></div>
				<div class="metric"><span class="metric-value">0</span><span class="metric-label">Data Stored</span></div>
				<div class="metric-divider"></div>
				<div class="metric"><span class="metric-value">3</span><span class="metric-label">Engines</span></div>
			</div>
		</div>
		
		<div class="scroll-hint" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 8px; clear: both; margin-top: 20px;">
			<span>Scroll to Calculate</span>
			<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" style="width: 24px; height: 24px;"><path d="M12 5v14M19 12l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
		</div>
	</section>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="currency-section">
		<div class="wrap">
			<p class="section-label">UNIVERSAL CURRENCY MATRIX</p>
			<p class="cur-instruction">Click the dropdown below to select your base currency from all 180 national currencies. Your selection applies across all three engines instantly.</p>
			<div class="cur-dropdown-wrap">
				<button class="cur-trigger" id="cur-trigger" aria-haspopup="listbox" aria-expanded="false">
					<span class="cur-t-sym" id="cur-t-sym">$</span>
					<span class="cur-t-divider"></span>
					<span class="cur-t-info">
						<span class="cur-t-name" id="cur-t-name">US Dollar</span>
						<span class="cur-t-code" id="cur-t-code">USD</span>
					</span>
					<svg class="cur-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" width="14" height="14"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
				</button>
				<div class="cur-panel" id="cur-panel" role="listbox" aria-label="Select currency" hidden>
					<div class="cur-search-wrap">
						<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" width="14" height="14" class="cur-search-icon"><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8"/><line x1="21" y1="21" x2="16.65" y2="16.65"/></svg>
						<input type="text" id="cur-search" class="cur-search" placeholder="Search by name or code (e.g. Euro, USD)..." autocomplete="off" spellcheck="false"/>
					</div>
					<div class="cur-list" id="cur-list"></div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="engine-section" id="networth">
		<div class="wrap">
			<div class="engine-header">
				<span class="engine-tag"><span class="badge-dot pulse"></span> ENGINE A</span>
				<h2>Sovereign Net Worth Calculator &amp; Report Generator</h2>
				<p>Calculate your true net worth by measuring total assets against total liabilities. Add custom categories to match your exact financial picture.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="two-col">
				<div class="panel">
					<div class="panel-head">
						<div><h3>Assets</h3><small>What you own</small></div>
						<div class="ptotal ppos"><small>TOTAL</small><span class="cs">$</span><span id="a-assets-hd">0</span></div>
					</div>
					<div class="rows-list" id="nw-assets">
						<div class="row-item"><label>Cash &amp; Savings</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi nw-asset" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
						<div class="row-item"><label>Stocks &amp; Securities</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi nw-asset" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
						<div class="row-item"><label>Real Estate</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi nw-asset" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
						<div class="row-item row-item--bullion">
							<div class="asset-picker-label">
								<span class="asset-picker-title">Bullion Metals</span>
								<div class="asset-picker" id="bullion-picker">
									<button type="button" class="ap-btn ap-active" data-code="XAU" data-sym="Au" data-name="Gold">
										<span class="ap-sym">Au</span><span class="ap-name">Gold</span>
									</button>
									<button type="button" class="ap-btn" data-code="XAG" data-sym="Ag" data-name="Silver">
										<span class="ap-sym">Ag</span><span class="ap-name">Silver</span>
									</button>
								</div>
							</div>
							<div class="field"><span class="cs bullion-cs">Au</span><input type="number" class="fi nw-asset" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div>
						</div>
						<div class="row-item row-item--crypto">
							<div class="asset-picker-label">
								<span class="asset-picker-title">Digital Assets</span>
								<div class="asset-picker" id="crypto-picker">
									<button type="button" class="ap-btn ap-crypto-btn ap-active" data-code="BTC" data-sym="₿" data-name="Bitcoin">
										<span class="ap-sym">₿</span><span class="ap-name">BTC</span>
									</button>
									<button type="button" class="ap-btn ap-crypto-btn" data-code="ETH" data-sym="Ξ" data-name="Ethereum">
										<span class="ap-sym">Ξ</span><span class="ap-name">ETH</span>
									</button>
									<button type="button" class="ap-btn ap-crypto-btn" data-code="SOL" data-sym="◎" data-name="Solana">
										<span class="ap-sym">◎</span><span class="ap-name">SOL</span>
									</button>
								</div>
							</div>
							<div class="field"><span class="cs crypto-cs">₿</span><input type="number" class="fi nw-asset" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div>
						</div>
					</div>
					<button class="add-btn" data-list="nw-assets" data-class="nw-asset">+ Add Asset</button>
					<div class="panel-foot pos-foot"><span>Total Assets</span><span class="fval fpos"><span class="cs">$</span><span id="nw-ta">0</span></span></div>
				</div>
				<div class="panel">
					<div class="panel-head">
						<div><h3>Liabilities</h3><small>What you owe</small></div>
						<div class="ptotal pneg"><small>TOTAL</small><span class="cs">$</span><span id="a-liab-hd">0</span></div>
					</div>
					<div class="rows-list" id="nw-liabilities">
						<div class="row-item"><label>Credit Card Debt</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi nw-liability" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
						<div class="row-item"><label>Student Loans</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi nw-liability" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
						<div class="row-item"><label>Mortgage / Home Loan</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi nw-liability" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
						<div class="row-item"><label>Auto / Vehicle Loan</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi nw-liability" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
					</div>
					<button class="add-btn" data-list="nw-liabilities" data-class="nw-liability">+ Add Liability</button>
					<div class="panel-foot neg-foot"><span>Total Liabilities</span><span class="fval fneg"><span class="cs">$</span><span id="nw-tl">0</span></span></div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="result-box" id="nw-result">
				<div class="rbox-bar"><span class="dot-r"></span><span class="dot-y"></span><span class="dot-g"></span><span class="rbox-lbl">NET WORTH</span></div>
				<div class="rbox-body">
					<div class="big-val"><span class="rcs cs">$</span><span id="nw-value">0</span></div>
					<p id="nw-tip">Enter your assets and liabilities to calculate net worth.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="exp-row"><button class="exp-btn" id="nw-pdf">Export PDF</button><button class="exp-btn" id="nw-csv">Export CSV</button></div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="engine-section alt-bg" id="cashflow">
		<div class="wrap">
			<div class="engine-header">
				<span class="engine-tag"><span class="badge-dot pulse"></span> ENGINE B</span>
				<h2>Monthly Cashflow Balance Calculator</h2>
				<p>Track your monthly income versus expenses to understand your financial velocity.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="concept-box">
				<h4>Understanding Cashflow</h4>
				<p>Cashflow measures how money moves in and out of your life every month. <strong>Positive cashflow</strong> means your income exceeds expenses — you have surplus to save or invest. <strong>Negative cashflow</strong> means you spend more than you earn, eroding wealth over time. Tracking monthly cashflow reveals where money leaks, cuts waste, and shows how much can be redirected toward investments or debt repayment each month. This is one of the most powerful habits of financially successful people.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="two-col">
				<div class="panel">
					<div class="panel-head">
						<div><h3>Monthly Income</h3><small>What flows in</small></div>
						<div class="ptotal ppos"><small>TOTAL</small><span class="cs">$</span><span id="cf-inc-hd">0</span></div>
					</div>
					<div class="rows-list" id="cf-income">
						<div class="row-item"><label>Salary / Wages</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi cf-inc" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
						<div class="row-item"><label>Freelance / Side Income</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi cf-inc" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
						<div class="row-item"><label>Investment Returns</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi cf-inc" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
					</div>
					<button class="add-btn" data-list="cf-income" data-class="cf-inc">+ Add Income</button>
					<div class="panel-foot pos-foot"><span>Total Monthly Income</span><span class="fval fpos"><span class="cs">$</span><span id="cf-ti">0</span></span></div>
				</div>
				<div class="panel">
					<div class="panel-head">
						<div><h3>Monthly Expenses</h3><small>What flows out</small></div>
						<div class="ptotal pneg"><small>TOTAL</small><span class="cs">$</span><span id="cf-exp-hd">0</span></div>
					</div>
					<div class="rows-list" id="cf-expenses">
						<div class="row-item"><label>Rent / Mortgage Payment</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi cf-exp" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
						<div class="row-item"><label>Utilities &amp; Bills</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi cf-exp" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
						<div class="row-item"><label>Food &amp; Groceries</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi cf-exp" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
						<div class="row-item"><label>Transportation</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi cf-exp" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
						<div class="row-item"><label>Subscriptions</label><div class="field"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" class="fi cf-exp" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
					</div>
					<button class="add-btn" data-list="cf-expenses" data-class="cf-exp">+ Add Expense</button>
					<div class="panel-foot neg-foot"><span>Total Monthly Expenses</span><span class="fval fneg"><span class="cs">$</span><span id="cf-te">0</span></span></div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="result-box" id="cf-result">
				<div class="rbox-bar"><span class="dot-r"></span><span class="dot-y"></span><span class="dot-g"></span><span class="rbox-lbl">MONTHLY CASHFLOW</span></div>
				<div class="rbox-body">
					<div class="big-val"><span class="rcs cs">$</span><span id="cf-value">0</span></div>
					<p id="cf-tip">Enter your income and monthly expenses to calculate cashflow.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="exp-row"><button class="exp-btn" id="cf-pdf">Export PDF</button><button class="exp-btn" id="cf-csv">Export CSV</button></div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="engine-section" id="projector">
		<div class="wrap">
			<div class="engine-header">
				<span class="engine-tag"><span class="badge-dot pulse"></span> ENGINE C</span>
				<h2>Interest Calculator &amp; Wealth Generator</h2>
				<p>Analyze investments with compound growth or calculate simple interest for loans &amp; savings. Responds to the Universal Currency Matrix above.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="calc-tabs">
				<button class="calc-tab active" data-tab="compound">
					<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" width="14" height="14"><polyline points="22 7 13.5 15.5 8.5 10.5 2 17"/><polyline points="16 7 22 7 22 13"/></svg>
					Compound Interest
				</button>
				<button class="calc-tab" data-tab="simple">
					<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" width="14" height="14"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><line x1="3" y1="9" x2="21" y2="9"/><line x1="9" y1="21" x2="9" y2="9"/></svg>
					Simple Interest
				</button>
			</div>

			<div class="tab-pane" id="tab-compound">
				<div class="proj-grid">
					<div class="proj-inputs">
						<div class="input-card"><h4>Starting Principal</h4><div class="field wide"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" id="principal" class="fi proj-inp" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
						<div class="input-card"><h4>Monthly Contribution</h4><div class="field wide"><span class="cs">$</span><input type="number" id="monthly" class="fi proj-inp" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div></div>
						<div class="input-card"><h4>Annual Return Rate</h4><div class="field wide"><input type="number" id="rate" class="fi proj-inp" placeholder="7" min="0" max="100" step="0.1"/><span class="sfx">%</span></div></div>
						<div class="input-card"><h4>Time Horizon</h4><div class="field wide"><input type="number" id="years" class="fi proj-inp" placeholder="10" min="1" max="50" step="1"/><span class="sfx">yrs</span></div></div>
					</div>
					<div class="proj-stats">
						<div class="pstat"><span class="psl">Total Invested</span><span class="psv" id="proj-invested"><span class="cs">$</span>0</span></div>
						<div class="pstat accent"><span class="psl">Interest Earned</span><span class="psv" id="proj-interest"><span class="cs">$</span>0</span></div>
						<div class="pstat total"><span class="psl">Future Value</span><span class="psv big" id="proj-future"><span class="cs">$</span>0</span></div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="graph-wrap">
					<h3 class="graph-title">10-Year Wealth Trajectory</h3>
					<p class="graph-sub">Consistent monthly contributions at compound growth</p>
					<div class="canvas-box"><canvas id="chart" width="800" height="300"></canvas></div>
					<div class="chart-leg">
						<span class="leg-i"><span class="leg-dot dgray"></span>Principal Invested</span>
						<span class="leg-i"><span class="leg-dot dgreen"></span>Total with Interest</span>
					</div>
					<div class="yr-stats" id="yr-stats"></div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="tab-pane" id="tab-simple" hidden>
				<div class="si-mode-row">
					<button class="si-mbtn si-active" data-mode="invest">
						<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" width="14" height="14"><polyline points="22 7 13.5 15.5 8.5 10.5 2 17"/><polyline points="16 7 22 7 22 13"/></svg>
						Investment
					</button>
					<button class="si-mbtn" data-mode="loan">
						<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" width="14" height="14"><rect x="1" y="4" width="22" height="16" rx="2"/><line x1="1" y1="10" x2="23" y2="10"/></svg>
						Loan
					</button>
				</div>
				<div class="concept-box">
					<h4 id="si-chead">Simple Interest &mdash; Investment Mode</h4>
					<p id="si-cbody">Calculates interest on the <strong>principal only</strong>. Ideal for fixed deposits, treasury bills, and short-term savings. Formula: <strong>SI = (P &times; R &times; T) / 100</strong></p>
				</div>
				<div class="proj-grid">
					<div class="proj-inputs">
						<div class="input-card">
							<h4>Principal Amount</h4>
							<div class="field wide"><span class="cs">$</span><input id="si-p" type="number" class="fi si-inp" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01"/></div>
						</div>
						<div class="input-card">
							<h4>Annual Interest Rate</h4>
							<div class="field wide"><input id="si-r" type="number" class="fi si-inp" placeholder="5" min="0" max="100" step="0.01"/><span class="sfx">%</span></div>
						</div>
						<div class="input-card">
							<h4>Time Period</h4>
							<div class="si-trow">
								<div class="field" style="flex:1;min-width:80px"><input id="si-t" type="number" class="fi si-inp" placeholder="3" min="0.1" step="0.1"/><span class="sfx" id="si-tsfx">yrs</span></div>
								<div class="si-tunit">
									<button class="si-tu si-tu-on" data-u="y">Yrs</button>
									<button class="si-tu" data-u="m">Mo</button>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="proj-stats">
						<div class="pstat"><span class="psl">Principal</span><span class="psv" id="sst-p"><span class="cs">$</span>0</span></div>
